claim.claim-text:
        1. A medical device for treating a sinus cavity, the medical device comprising:
a delivery system comprising a cannula and a pusher;
the cannula having a cannula proximal end, a cannula distal end, and defining a first cannula opening, a second cannula opening, and a cannula lumen extending between the first cannula opening and the second cannula opening;the pusher having a pusher proximal end, and a pusher distal end slidably disposed in the cannula lumen;a catheter having at least a portion disposed in the cannula lumen, the catheter having a catheter proximal end, a catheter distal end, a catheter wall, a catheter length extending between the catheter proximal end and the catheter distal end, and defining a first catheter opening, a second catheter opening, a first bend, a coil, a plurality of apertures, and a catheter lumen extending between the first catheter opening and the second catheter opening, each aperture of the plurality of apertures extending through the catheter wall and in communication with the catheter lumen;wherein the pusher distal end is adapted to engage with the catheter proximal end to transfer axial movement to the catheter; andwherein the catheter is adapted to move between a first configuration in which the portion of the catheter disposed within the cannula lumen is substantially straight when disposed in the cannula lumen and a second configuration in which the catheter defines the first bend and the coil along the catheter length when the catheter is free of the cannula lumen.

        13. A medical device for treating a sinus cavity, the medical device comprising:
a delivery system comprising a cannula and a pusher;
the cannula having a cannula proximal end, a cannula distal end, and defining a first cannula opening, a second cannula opening, and a cannula lumen extending between the first cannula opening and the second cannula opening;the pusher having a pusher proximal end, and a pusher distal end slidably disposed in the cannula lumen;a catheter having at least a portion disposed in the cannula lumen, the catheter having a catheter proximal end, a catheter distal end, a catheter wall, a catheter length extending between the catheter proximal end and the catheter distal end, a marker, and defining a first catheter opening, a second catheter opening, a first bend, a coil, a plurality of apertures, and a catheter lumen extending between the first catheter opening and the second catheter opening, the marker disposed at the first bend, each aperture of the plurality of apertures extending through the catheter wall and in communication with the catheter lumen;wherein the pusher distal end is adapted to engage with the catheter proximal end to transfer axial movement to the catheter; andwherein the catheter is adapted to move between a first configuration in which the portion of the catheter disposed within the cannula lumen is substantially straight when disposed in the cannula lumen and a second configuration in which the catheter defines the first bend and the coil along the catheter length when the catheter is free of the cannula lumen, the coil defined between the first bend and the catheter distal end.

        20. A medical device for treating a sinus cavity, the medical device comprising:
a delivery system comprising a cannula and a pusher;
the cannula having a cannula proximal end, a cannula distal end, and defining a first cannula opening, a second cannula opening, and a cannula lumen extending between the first cannula opening and the second cannula opening;the pusher having a pusher proximal end, and a pusher distal end slidably disposed in the cannula lumen;a catheter having at least a portion disposed in the cannula lumen, the catheter having a catheter proximal end, a catheter distal end, a catheter wall, a catheter length extending between the catheter proximal end and the catheter distal end, a marker, and defining a first catheter opening, a second catheter opening, a first bend, a second bend, a coil, a plurality of apertures, and a catheter lumen extending between the first catheter opening and the second catheter opening, the marker disposed at the first bend, each aperture of the plurality of apertures extending through the catheter wall and in communication with the catheter lumen;wherein the pusher distal end is adapted to engage with the catheter proximal end to transfer axial movement to the catheter;wherein the catheter is adapted to move between a first configuration in which the portion of the catheter disposed within the cannula lumen is substantially straight when disposed in the cannula lumen and a second configuration in which the catheter defines the first bend, the second bend, and the coil along the catheter length when the catheter is free of the cannula lumen, the second bend defined between the first bend and the coil, the coil defined between the second bend and the catheter distal end and having an outwardly facing side and an inwardly facing side; andwherein in the second configuration the catheter defines the plurality of apertures such that a first set of apertures of the plurality of apertures is disposed on the outwardly facing side of the coil and a second set of apertures of the plurality of apertures is disposed on the inwardly facing side of the coil.
